Experiment 3: Print Labels in MS Word

1. Open the Labels Feature:

Go to Mailings > Labels.



2. Select the Label Options:

Click Options and choose your label vendor and product number (or create a custom label if your size isnâ€™t listed).



3. Enter Label Text:

In the Address box, type the text you want to appear on the label. For example:

Company Name
123 Business Rd.
Industry City, XY 67890



4. Print the Labels:

Choose Full page of the same label if you want all labels identical.

Click Print or New Document to save and edit further.

